                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-755" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HOARE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, B</hi> 93.) The prisoner told me, on 2nd Dec., that he had lost the money.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471213-name-756" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-756" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-756" type="surname" value="SHARPLIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-756" type="given" value="JOHN JAMES"></interp>JOHN JAMES SHARPLIN</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> He told me next day that he had lost the money—I found him at a booking-office at Queenhithe—he said he had been robbed.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was to have brought the flat of butter back, but Mr. Phillips was from home—in going home I fell in with a young woman, who took me home, and picked my pockets of all the money, and 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. more which I had in my pocket—I met a policeman, who told me to go to the station.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471213-name-757" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-757" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-757" type="surname" value="HOARE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-757" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HOARE</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> He came to me on the morning of 2nd Dec., and said he had been robbed by a female who he went home with, that she got up in the night, and left him in bed.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471213-name-758" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-758" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-758" type="surname" value="BENNETT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-758" type="given" value="SUSANNAH"></interp>SUSANNAH BENNETT</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> He could not have had the butter that night—if he had paid the money, I should have received it—I do not know whether he was aware of that.</p>
